FILE: A crime scene cordoned off. Flickr.com/Adam Gerard JOHANNESBURG -  eNCA is focusing on various crimes and their effect on South African communities. READ: Police on high alert in Alexandra Alexandra is one of the areas in Gauteng with a high crime rate. In March, some residents in Alexandra planned a total shutdown in protest over rising crime levels. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 Meanwhile, one Cape Town community is calling for action against a Nigerian national, who allegedly committed sexual acts with under-aged girls. Images of this were shared widely on social media, causing widespread outrage. A protest regarding the matter is also planned outside the Parklands police station. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has more details. Courtesy #DStv403